<item>
            <title>[BEAM-9660] StreamingDataflowWorker has confusing exception on commits over 2GB</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BEAM-9660</link>
                <project id="12319527" key="BEAM">Beam</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Commits over 2GB have a negative serialized commit size.&lt;br/&gt;
When not using streaming engine the max commit limit is 2GB.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/beam/blob/v2.19.0/runners/google-cloud-dataflow-java/worker/src/main/java/org/apache/beam/runners/dataflow/worker/StreamingDataflowWorker.java#L450&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/beam/blob/v2.19.0/runners/google-cloud-dataflow-java/worker/src/main/java/org/apache/beam/runners/dataflow/worker/StreamingDataflowWorker.java#L450&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
There appears to be a logging regression introduced by&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/beam/pull/10013&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/beam/pull/10013&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With the new code, if the serialization overflows the estimated bytes is set to Integer.MAX which equals the commit limit for appliance.&lt;br/&gt;
Then the comparison here:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/beam/blob/v2.19.0/runners/google-cloud-dataflow-java/worker/src/main/java/org/apache/beam/runners/dataflow/worker/StreamingDataflowWorker.java#L1371&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/beam/blob/v2.19.0/runners/google-cloud-dataflow-java/worker/src/main/java/org/apache/beam/runners/dataflow/worker/StreamingDataflowWorker.java#L1371&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
which uses &amp;gt; does not trigger and the large commit is just passed on to the commit queue, triggering the exception seen in #3 &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;2&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; when the weigher uses the negative serialized size for the semaphore acquire call. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So previously where we would have thrown a KeyCommitTooLargeException we are throwing the IllegalArgumentException.&lt;br/&gt;
From that exception description: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/beam/blob/v2.19.0/runners/google-cloud-dataflow-java/worker/src/main/java/org/apache/beam/runners/dataflow/worker/StreamingDataflowWorker.java#L236&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/beam/blob/v2.19.0/runners/google-cloud-dataflow-java/worker/src/main/java/org/apache/beam/runners/dataflow/worker/StreamingDataflowWorker.java#L236&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
          &quot;. This may be caused by grouping a very &quot;&lt;br/&gt;
              + &quot;large amount of data in a single window without using Combine,&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
              + &quot; or by producing a large amount of data from a single input element.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The overflow could be remembered explicitly instead of just comparing with max.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
